Michelia doltsopa

   [7746.jpg]
    Authority   (Jacq.) Milne-Redh.
      Family    Magnoliopsida:Magnoliidae:Magnoliales:Magnoliaceae
     Synonyms
   Common names
      Editor
   Ecocrop code 7746

   Notes
   SOURCES (M. doltsopa Buch. Ham. ex DC.)
   Rashid M 1975 pp 103-110 [TEMP, RAIN, TEXT, DRA, PH, FER, LIG, USE]
   KILLING T
   Somewhat frost-hardy.
   GROWING PERIOD
   Perennial deciduous tree. In India, the majority of trees flower in
   March and seeds ripen in October-November.
   COMMON NAMES
   Champ, Gok, Dieng-rai, Sigurip, Penre, Bara champ, Safed Champ, Seti
   champ, Seto champ, Mithe Champ, Rani champ.
   FURTHER INF
   Scientific synonym: M. excelsa. In India, the tree can be found at
   elevations between 1500 and 2400 m, but it is best grown between
   1800-2250 m. Champ is adapted to a relative humidity in July of 80-90%
   and in January 70-90%. The tree can reach a height of 30-36 m.

   Sources

   FAO - Food and Agriculture Organization of the UN - Helping to build a
   world without hunger
